### StreamController Basics

`StreamController` provides manual control over a stream. You can add events, errors, and close the stream programmatically.

```dart
import 'dart:async';

void main() {
  var controller = StreamController<int>();

  // Listen to the stream
  controller.stream.listen(
    (data) => print('Data: $data'),
    onDone: () => print('Stream closed'),
  );

  // Add events
  controller.add(1);
  controller.add(2);
  controller.add(3);

  // Close the stream
  controller.close();
}
```

### Types of StreamControllers

| Type | Behavior |
|------|----------|
| Single-subscription | One listener only (default) |
| Broadcast | Multiple listeners allowed |

```dart
void main() {
  // Broadcast controller
  var controller = StreamController<int>.broadcast();

  var sub1 = controller.stream.listen((d) => print('Listener 1: $d'));
  var sub2 = controller.stream.listen((d) => print('Listener 2: $d'));

  controller.add(42);
  controller.add(100);
  controller.close();
}
```

### Adding Data and Errors

```dart
void main() {
  var controller = StreamController<String>();

  controller.stream.listen(
    (data) => print('Received: $data'),
    onError: (error) => print('Error: $error'),
    onDone: () => print('Done'),
  );

  controller.add('Hello');
  controller.addError('Something went wrong');
  controller.add('World');
  controller.close();
}
```

### Practical Example: Event Bus

```dart
class EventBus {
  final _controller = StreamController<dynamic>.broadcast();

  Stream<dynamic> get stream => _controller.stream;

  void emit(dynamic event) => _controller.add(event);

  void dispose() => _controller.close();
}

void main() {
  var bus = EventBus();

  bus.stream.listen((event) => print('Received: $event'));

  bus.emit('User logged in');
  bus.emit({'type': 'notification', 'data': 'New message'});
}
```

### Sink Property

```dart
void main() {
  var controller = StreamController<int>();

  // Sink is the input side
  controller.sink.add(1);
  controller.sink.add(2);

  // Stream is the output side
  controller.stream.listen(print);

  controller.sink.close();
}
```

> **Key Point:** Use `StreamController` when you need programmatic control over event emission. Use `.broadcast()` for multi-listener scenarios. Always close the controller when done to free resources.

codeExample:
import 'dart:async';

class SearchService {
  final _controller = StreamController<String>.broadcast();

  Stream<String> get searchResults => _controller.stream;

  void search(String query) {
    if (query.isEmpty) return;
    print('Searching for: $query');
    _controller.add('Results for $query');
  }

  void dispose() {
    _controller.close();
  }
}

void main() {
  var searchService = SearchService();

  searchService.searchResults.listen(
    (result) => print('Got: $result'),
  );

  searchService.search('Dart');
  searchService.search('Flutter');

  searchService.dispose();
}
